        "intro_text": "<p>Your lymphatic system is your body's internal cleaning crew—a network of vessels that processes <strong>3-4 liters of cellular waste and excess fluid every single day.</strong></p>",
        "intro_working": "When it's working properly, you don't even know it exists.",
        "callout_estrogen": "<p>But after age 35, declining estrogen hijacks this system's ability to function.</p>",
        "instead_text": "Instead of processing and removing waste, it backs up in your tissues.",
        "anatomy_image": "shopify://shop_images/imgi_13_LymphDrainageREWAMPEDvisualsArtboard13_32c9af9c-8847-44b0-aa75-e2a4485a459e.jpg",
        "accumulates_heading": "And it accumulates. Day after day. Week after week.",
        "accumulates_body": "<p>That gallon of fluid your body should be draining every 24 hours? It's pooling in your stomach, your legs, your face—anywhere gravity and tissue structure allow it to settle.</p>",
        "callout_waste": "<p>The metabolic waste your cells produce overnight? It's still sitting there at noon. At dinner. While you're trying to fall asleep.</p>",
        "cells_sitting": "<p><strong>Your cells are literally sitting in their own waste—and your body can't flush it out.</strong></p>",
        "longer_text": "The longer this goes on, the worse it gets. More congestion. More inflammation. More pressure on an already compromised system.",
        "color_scheme": "",
        "padding_top": 0,
